  "text": "In Type 2 AIP, the affected pancreas demonstrates neutrophilic infiltration in the ductal epithelium with duct destruction and occasionally microabscess formation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The histology is characterized by the classic ductal granulocyte epithelial lesion.",
